                  ] which our Translatours turn [under it], that is, under the Levitical Priest-hood, some understand [with it] [,and [about the same time] the people received, or were subjected to the Law. Junius translates it, and Vatablus expounds it differently from the rest, in this manner. For it, that is, for Sanctification the people received the Priest-hood, or the Law of Priest-hood: and so referr the Relative [It] not to Priest-hood, but to perfection or sanctification; and, with them, the Preposition [
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
